14/04/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Jalal Talabani, a leader of the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan, told CNN on Sunday (13 April) that Turkish observers would be welcome to inspect the situation in northern Iraq.
He added that the Kurds have abided by the agreement to pull out of Kirkuk, leaving it under the control of US forces.
In other news Sunday, Israeli Foreign Minister Silvan Shalom arrived in Turkey to meet with his counterpart Abdullah Gul.
The focus of Monday's talks will be the consequences of the war in Iraq.
(AFP, Anadolu Agency - 13/04/03)
